        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 10 at 5:06PM PDT by NWS Spokane WA</headline>
        <description>At 506 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Pinehurst. These storms were nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pinehurst, Kingston, and Cataldo.

This includes Interstate 90 in Idaho between mile markers 38 and 47.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
